		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">Mark Brazaitis</span></strong> is the author of six books, including <em>The Incurables: Stories</em>, which won the 2012 Sullivan Prize in Short Fiction and the 2013 Devil&rsquo;s Kitchen Reading Award. He was recently drafted to play Cinderella&rsquo;s father opposite his younger daughter in an ice-skating production. His role consisted of doing a spin on two feet, then falling onto the ice. He lives in Morgantown, West Virginia.</p><a href="/contributors/mark-brazaitis" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
